# Short Editor environment variables
#
# Local development: `.env.development` is loaded automatically by `next dev`.
# Production builds: use `npm run build:dev|stg|demo|prod` which inline the
# correct `NEXT_PUBLIC_ALLOWED_CMS_ORIGINS` per environment, so you do NOT
# need a `.env.production` file in source control.
# Override locally with `.env.local` when needed (gitignored by Next.js).

# Comma-separated list of CMS origins allowed to talk to the editor via postMessage.
# Required for embed mode to work. When empty, inbound postMessage events are
# silently dropped (fail-secure).
# Examples:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_ALLOWED_CMS_ORIGINS=https://cms.tigmedia.jp
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_ALLOWED_CMS_ORIGINS=https://cms.stg.tigmedia.jp,http://localhost:8080
NEXT_PUBLIC_ALLOWED_CMS_ORIGINS=
